Interior CS Joseph Nkaissery has declared 90 groups criminal and has outlawed them. This means any member of the banned groups can be arrested and charged under the Prevention of Organised Crimes Act, 2010.The law aims at enhancing the prevention, investigation, and punishment of organised crimes in the country. Among those named in the notice include Wakali Kwanza, based on the Coast, the Gaza gang, which operates in Kayole, Superpower in Eastleigh and 42 Brothers, based in Eastlands.Other outlawed groups are:Read: Majengo, Kisauni juvenile gangs put on notice as crime increasesAlso read: Kisumu gangs out on notice